Explanation

Passing Context

context: { $implicit: user, index: i }


$implicit: user → makes user the default input for the template.

index: i → passes the loop index as a named variable.

Capturing Context with let-

<ng-template #userTemplate let-person let-idx="index">


let-person → captures $implicit (so person = user).

let-idx="index" → captures the index property.

Usage in Template

{{ idx + 1 }}. {{ person.name }} - {{ person.role }}


idx is the loop index (0,1,2).

person is the user object.